* Footnotes
[fn:fn1] REgarding the basic or simple passive In Jagarôth, /-ax/ is used first to form a past participle like /thiktax/ a touched thing. It /has already been touched/ ergo its inherent aspect is the perfective apspect. Therefore a conjugated verb like /thiktaxâlos/ is /perfect/ passive. There really is not simple passive conjugation, but the perfect passive is used more or less indifferently as a simple passive and a perfect passive both. The difference is not heard in Jagarôth. See [[jed]] and [[flet]].


